"""
Record a meeting with realtime transcription via parakeet-mlx.

Captures microphone audio to FLAC (durable backup) and transcribes via
parakeet streaming. Three artifacts land in $MEETING_DIR (default
~/recordings/):

  <name>.flac    audio backup, playable mid-recording
  <name>.md      structured transcript (frontmatter + sections), fsync'd per chunk
  <name>.txt     plain transcript, fsync'd per chunk
  <name>.log     ffmpeg + script stderr

A localhost web page also opens automatically with a live-updating view.

Usage:
    recorder [name]            # name defaults to YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS
    recorder --no-browser      # don't auto-open the live page
    recorder --port 8765       # pin a port (default: ephemeral)
    recorder --device ":1"     # override avfoundation audio device
    recorder --list-devices    # list devices and exit
    recorder --from-file f.wav # transcribe an existing file (no mic)

To chat about the transcript in Claude Code mid-meeting or after:
    @~/recordings/<name>.md  what were the action items?

The .md file rewrites on every transcript update, so referencing it
during a live meeting always reads the current state.

Crash safety:
    - FLAC has -flush_packets 1, playable on kill -9
    - .md and .txt are fsync'd after every finalized-token batch
    - worst-case loss on hard kill is one ~2s chunk
"""
